You are implementing the central shared TypeScript type definitions for a video production pipeline editor built with Next.js 15 App Router. This module (`lib/types.ts`) is the single source of truth for all domain types ‚Äî pipeline stages, job states, annotations, sections, and project configuration ‚Äî used across every frontend component, API route, and server library. No other module may define these types; all imports flow from here with no circular dependencies.

Requirements
1. Export the `PipelineStage` union type covering all 10 pipeline stages: `'setup' | 'script' | 'tts-script' | 'tts-render' | 'audio-sync' | 'specs' | 'veo' | 'compositions' | 'render' | 'audit'`.
2. Export `StageStatus` union: `'not_started' | 'running' | 'done' | 'error'`.
3. Export `JobStatus` union: `'pending' | 'running' | 'done' | 'error'`.
4. Export `Job` interface: `{ id: string; stage: PipelineStage; status: JobStatus; progress: number; error: string | null; params: Record<string, unknown>; createdAt: string; updatedAt: string }`.
5. Export `FixType` union: `'remotion' | 'veo' | 'tts' | 'none'`.
6. Export `AnnotationAnalysis` interface: `{ severity: 'critical' | 'major' | 'minor' | 'pass'; fixType: FixType; technicalAssessment: string; suggestedFixes: string[]; confidence: number }`.
7. Export `Annotation` interface: `{ id: string; sectionId: string; timestamp: number; text: string; videoFile: string | null; drawingDataUrl: string | null; compositeDataUrl: string | null; analysis: AnnotationAnalysis | null; resolved: boolean; resolveJobId: string | null; createdAt: string }`.
8. Export `Section` interface: `{ id: string; label: string; videoFile: string; specDir: string; remotionDir: string; compositionId: string; durationSeconds: number; offsetSeconds: number }`.
9. Export `TtsConfig` interface: `{ voice: string; rate: number; model: string }`.
10. Export `VeoConfig` interface: `{ model: string; aspectRatio: '16:9' | '9:16'; referenceImages: Record<string, string> }`.
11. Export `RenderConfig` interface: `{ maxParallelRenders: number; outputDir: string; fps: number; width: number; height: number }`.
12. Export `AudioSyncConfig` interface: `{ sectionGroups: Record<string, string[]> }`.
13. Export `ProjectConfig` interface: `{ name: string; outputResolution: '1920x1080' | '1280x720'; tts: TtsConfig; sections: Section[]; audioSync: AudioSyncConfig; veo: VeoConfig; render: RenderConfig }`.
14. Export `RenderProgress` interface: `{ percent: number; message: string }`.
15. Export `ClaudeFixResult` interface: `{ fixType: FixType; filesModified: string[]; changeDescription: string; confidence: number }`.
16. Export `AnnotationCaptureData` interface used by VideoPlayer: `{ timestamp: number; text: string; drawingDataUrl: string | null; compositeDataUrl: string | null; videoFile: string }`.
17. Export `SseSend` type alias: `(data: object) => void`.
18. All types must be pure TypeScript ‚Äî no runtime code, no imports from other local modules.
19. Use `interface` for object shapes and `type` for unions/aliases. Export every definition named above.

Dependencies

No local dependencies.

Instructions
- Create `lib/types.ts` exporting all types listed above as named exports.
- Group exports logically: (1) pipeline stage/status enums, (2) job types, (3) annotation types, (4) section and project config types, (5) utility/helper types.
- Add a JSDoc comment on each exported type explaining its purpose in one line.
- Do not import from any other local file ‚Äî this module must have zero local dependencies to avoid circular imports.
- The `AnnotationAnalysis` type is returned by Claude analysis invocations and must align with the JSON schema Claude is prompted to return.
- `ProjectConfig.sections` is an array; ordering matters for ffmpeg concat and audio offset calculations.
- `SseSend` is used as a parameter type in `lib/jobs.ts` ‚Äî define it here so it's shared.
- Ensure `RenderProgress` matches what `lib/render.ts` callbacks emit.

Deliverable
- `lib/types.ts` ‚Äî production-ready TypeScript file with all types exported, no runtime code, no imports.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- `Job.params` stores stage-specific invocation parameters as an opaque record (serialized to/from SQLite as JSON text).
- `Section.videoFile` is a relative path from the project root to the rendered MP4.
- `AnnotationAnalysis.confidence` is a float 0‚Äì1.
- `ProjectConfig` matches the on-disk `project.json` shape exactly; Zod validation in `lib/project.ts` will validate against this interface.

Please produce production-ready prompt content that will generate the module consistent with the above.
